Durban - Days after a successful sting at the police living quarters at the Durban Central Police Station on Friday morning, another raid was undertaken at police accommodation residence Excelsior Court in the early hours of Monday morning.

Police spokesperson, Brigadier Jay Naicker said police officers from the Public Order Police, National Intervention Unit, Tactical Response Team, Flying Squad, K9 and DPCI swooped into Excelsior Court in search of those who do not belong there as well as to root out any illegal activity taking place in this particular quarters.AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
Also see: PICS: Scores nabbed in SAPS building raid

"These police officers searched every room in the building and arrested twenty six (26) trespassers. Twenty one (21) of those arrested were not police officials and could not provide a reasonable explanation for being on the premises. All arrested suspect were charged for trespassing and were served with a R300-00 admission of guilt fine." said Naicker










